<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-708-058  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 708 058.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  August 6 1990 n478 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM scheme targets data center control.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cortese, Amy; Sperling, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM will soon introduce HostView, its latest system managementarchitecture and repository.andP;  As with its applications developmentarchitecture, AD/Cycle, IBM will continue to seek the support ofsoftware vendors for the management scheme and even for theprovision of key pieces.andP;  IBM has begun negotiations with variouspotential partners.andP;  The management architecture will encompass abroad range of data center activities, including network andoperations management, security, and problem and changemanagement.andP;  It will provide automated operations.andP;  The repositorywill store information needed to manage a company's operationsthrough two levels: one geared to policy and administration andanother for storing information needed for management tasks.andP;  AnOS-2-based workstation will be the window into the repository andthe point from which the data center and networks are to bemanaged.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product development).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Third-Party VendorsComputer Systems IntegrationNetwork Management SoftwareProduct DevelopmentSoftware ArchitectureInformation CentersBusiness Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>